The paper deals with the analysis of SINR outage probability in wireless cellular networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of stochastic geometric modeling and moment generating functions also suggests a possible categorization under machine learning (cs.MA) and statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the application of Charlier expansion and saddle point method may also relate to game theory (cs.GT).
